<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta charSet="utf-8" data-next-head=""/><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" data-next-head=""/><title data-next-head="">How Austen and Darwin converged on the question of beauty | Aeon Essays</title><meta name="robots" content="index,follow,max-image-preview:large" data-next-head=""/><meta name="description" content="Charles Darwin was as fascinated by extravagant ornament in nature as Jane Austen was in culture. Did their explanations agree?" data-next-head=""/><meta property="og:title" content="How Austen and Darwin converged on the question of beauty | Aeon Essays" data-next-head=""/><meta property="og:description" content="Charles Darwin was as fascinated by extravagant ornament in nature as Jane Austen was in culture. Did their explanations agree?" data-next-head=""/><meta property="og:url" content="https://aeon.co/essays/how-austen-and-darwin-converged-on-the-question-of-beauty" data-next-head=""/><meta property="og:type" content="article" data-next-head=""/><meta property="og:image" content="https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/67725c32-b102-4f68-adaa-0c7f06687b4e/essay-final-austen_and_darwin_5.jpg?width=1200&amp;quality=75&amp;format=auto" data-next-head=""/><meta property="og:image:alt" content="&lt;p&gt;Illustration by &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.richard-wilkinson.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;Richard Wilkinson&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" data-next-head=""/><meta property="og:image:width" content="2000" data-next-head=""/><meta property="og:image:height" content="1252" data-next-head=""/><link rel="canonical" href="https://aeon.co/essays/how-austen-and-darwin-converged-on-the-question-of-beauty" data-next-head=""/><meta name="theme-color" content="#0c776d" data-next-head=""/><meta name="twitter:label1" content="Reading time" data-next-head=""/><meta name="twitter:data1" content="21 min read" data-next-head=""/><link rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" title="